column5: But let us take a minute to wish everyone born on February 29th a very Happy Birthday! They don't hear those words as often as they should y'know. Just remember that even if you only have 25% of the birthdays for the same number of years, you still OLD BUGGARS!
Good point, happy birthday leap year babies
Not sure if we can say it's coming in like a lamb here----kinda cold
Happy March 1st for sure, I became a country bumkin exacatly 1 year ago today
I just missed that sweet leap year birthday deal.I would be 12.75 years old if my Mom had planned stuff out better.
Glad february is gone...closer to spring!!!  Only 31 more days until baseball opening day!
Well Happy Happy to ya JOE!!!!!!!!!!!! It's pretty bad when I know your goats' birthdays but not yours.
But then you would not be legal drinking age!
Todays announcement from Enviroment Canada is for a COLD spring not at all like last year.Lets hope they are WRONG as usual.  vance
Not a moment to soon, Roy.  Fishing in February (catching, anyways) sucked...got nailed by the "ole" skunk a few times!!
Thanx Roy,one more month untill Rockets birthday!
How old IS the Rocket now, Joe? In homo sapien time I mean....
I think he was born in 1997 or 1998.Many goats dont see their 10th birtday but he comes from sturdy lines.His Mom is still with us.
March means one thing to me,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,  NCAA MARCH MADNESS.
